Requirements

Android device with at least 4GB of RAM and sufficient storage space.
Termux installed from F-Droid. Avoid Termux from the Play Store as itâ€™s outdated.
A stable internet connection.

Steps to Install and Setup NetHunter

1. Update Termux and Install Required Packages
First, update Termux and install the necessary dependencies:


pkg update && pkg upgrade -y
pkg install wget curl proot git -y


2. Download and Install the Kali NetHunter Chroot
Use the official NetHunter script to install Kali Linux.
1. Download the NetHunter installation script:


wget -O install-nethunter-termux https://offs.ec/2MceZWr
chmod +x install-nethunter-termux


2. Run the script to install NetHunter:

./install-nethunter-termux

The script will download and set up the full NetHunter environment.

Choose the appropriate Kali rootfs image (minimal or full) depending on your storage space and requirements.





---

3. Launch the Kali NetHunter Environment

Once the installation is complete, you can access the NetHunter session using:

n

